::Shadow Wing::

She turned and faced him.  She was mad. Not at him, but at herself.
"Look, you showed me how lousy a fighter I am.  How I'm nothing more than an 
easy target." She was starting to let her emotions take over completely.  
"You could have killed me in the forest.  You could have shot me. I could be 
dead. You..you proved just how weak I am. How useless I am.  You opened my 
eyes as to how I am so stupid in a fight. I tried to be something I'm not.  
I wanted to be a fighter.  I tried to prove to myself that I could be. And 
you proved that I am no fighter.  Hell, I'm not good at hiding even. You and 
that Pred found me easily enough. Matrix knows how I survived in the forest 
by myself all that time."  She fell to her knees and wept.  Her was mad that 
her spark was so damned emotional.  She was more of her animal counterpart, 
than a techno-logicle being.
"Please just take me back to the base and have me reprogrammed or scrapped."
